==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petitory
<hw>Pet"i*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>petitorius</ets>, fr. <ets>petere</ets>, <ets>petitum</ets>, to
beg, ask: cf. F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧titore</ets>.]</ety> <def>Petitioning;
soliciting; supplicating.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Petitory suit</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Petitory action</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Admiralty Law)</fld>,
<cd>a suit in which the mere title to property is litigated and sought
to be enforced, as distinguished from a <contr>possessory suit</contr>;
also <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>, a suit wherein the plaintiff claims
something as due him by the defendant.</cd>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petong</ent>⟦br⟧
